Network Defense & Countermeasures ‚Äì Session 2
BASIC MCQs (1‚Äì10)
1. Risk management in Information Security primarily involves:
A. Eliminating all threats
B. Identifying, assessing, and controlling risks
C. Installing firewalls only
D. Monitoring network traffic

2. Exposure in security terminology refers to:
A. Presence of attackers
B. Potential loss due to a threat
C. Actual exploitation
D. Security policy violation

3. Which of the following is an example of a countermeasure?
A. Vulnerability
B. Threat actor
C. Firewall
D. Exploit code

4. A firewall is mainly used to:
A. Encrypt data
B. Authenticate users
C. Control network traffic based on rules
D. Scan vulnerabilities

5. Which firewall component examines source/destination IP and port numbers?
A. Application layer gateway
B. Packet-filtering firewall
C. Proxy firewall
D. IDS

6. DMZ stands for:
A. Distributed Management Zone
B. Data Monitoring Zone
C. Demilitarized Zone
D. Dynamic Management Zone

7. The primary purpose of a DMZ is to:
A. Improve internet speed
B. Protect internal network from external users
C. Eliminate firewall rules
D. Replace IDS

8. Which system is commonly placed inside a DMZ?
A. Database server
B. Internal file server
C. Public web server
D. Domain controller

9. Packet-filtering firewalls mainly operate at which OSI layer?
A. Physical
B. Data Link
C. Network & Transport
D. Application

10. pfSense is best described as:
A. Commercial IDS
B. Linux-based router
C. Open-source firewall and routing platform
D. Antivirus software

INTERMEDIATE MCQs (11‚Äì20)
11. According to the NIST Cybersecurity Framework, which function involves risk identification?
A. Protect
B. Detect
C. Identify
D. Respond

12. Risk exposure is typically calculated as:
A. Threat √ó Vulnerability
B. Asset value √ó Impact
C. Likelihood √ó Impact
D. Vulnerability √ó Countermeasure

13. Which firewall type creates a full connection on behalf of the client?
A. Packet filter
B. Stateful firewall
C. Proxy firewall
D. Circuit-level gateway

14. One major advantage of proxy firewalls over packet filters is:
A. Higher speed
B. Lower latency
C. Application-level inspection
D. Simpler configuration

15. In pfSense, which interface is usually connected to the internet?
A. LAN
B. OPT
C. DMZ
D. WAN

16. A DMZ with three-legged firewall architecture has:
A. One interface
B. Two interfaces
C. Three interfaces
D. Multiple firewalls only

17. Which attack is a DMZ specifically designed to limit?
A. Insider threat
B. Malware execution
C. Direct access to internal network
D. Password reuse

18. iptables is mainly used to implement:
A. Proxy firewall
B. Packet-filtering firewall
C. IDS
D. VPN

19. Squid is commonly used as:
A. Packet sniffer
B. Web proxy firewall
C. Vulnerability scanner
D. Load balancer

20. Which firewall method inspects packet state information?
A. Stateless firewall
B. Packet filter
C. Stateful inspection firewall
D. Proxy firewall

ADVANCED MCQs (21‚Äì30)
21. An organization hosting a public web server should place it in a DMZ primarily to:
A. Improve website speed
B. Reduce firewall rules
C. Isolate compromise from internal network
D. Eliminate attacks

22. In NIST framework-based risk analysis, which step follows risk identification?
A. Risk elimination
B. Risk prioritization and treatment
C. Risk ignoring
D. Risk transfer only

23. Packet-filtering firewalls are vulnerable to which limitation?
A. Cannot inspect headers
B. Lack application-layer awareness
C. High resource consumption
D. Cannot block IP addresses

24. A proxy firewall provides stronger security mainly because it:
A. Uses faster routing
B. Hides internal IP addresses
C. Performs deep packet inspection at application layer
D. Requires fewer rules

25. In pfSense DMZ configuration, which rule is MOST critical?
A. Allow all traffic from DMZ to LAN
B. Block DMZ to LAN by default
C. Allow LAN to WAN only
D. Disable NAT

26. If an attacker compromises a DMZ web server, what is the expected security outcome?
A. Full LAN compromise
B. No impact at all
C. Limited access due to isolation
D. Automatic firewall shutdown

27. Which metric best helps prioritize firewall rules in risk-based design?
A. Bandwidth usage
B. Asset criticality
C. Network latency
D. Packet size

28. Stateful firewalls improve security by:
A. Blocking all inbound traffic
B. Tracking session state
C. Acting as proxy servers
D. Encrypting packets

29. Comparing iptables and Squid, which statement is correct?
A. Both operate at network layer
B. iptables is application-layer only
C. Squid provides application-level proxying
D. Squid replaces firewall rules

30. From CDAC exam perspective, which statement is MOST accurate?
A. Firewalls eliminate risk completely
B. DMZ replaces need for firewall
C. Firewalls are one of multiple countermeasures
D. Proxy firewalls are obsolete

